    "> ðŸ’¡ One important thing to notice is that in order to make the movements of the head and arms synchronized, we need NOT to wait for the end of the movements of the head when we start the movements of the arms (hence the *wait=False* argument in the *look_at* calls). \n",
    "> Same goes for the arms, if we wait for the end of the movement, let's say of the left arm before starting the right arm, the movements will be desynchronized.\n",
